This paper addresses the problem of bias in automated face recognition algorithms, which is a common issue in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves the use of adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential security implications of biased face recognition, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that involve the use of multimedia data, which is relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
